{panel:title=Original Description| titleBGColor=#3672B0| titleColor=#FFFFFF}
Searching for 'text ~ foo' gives responses as expected. Since there are tickets which do not contain the string 'foo' I'd expect the query 'NOT text ~ foo' to give results, however I get nothing.

Looking at the request log in Firefox I see:
{noformat}
[15:03:04.031] GET https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/Search!Jql.jspa?decorator=none&jql=not+text+~+foo&_=1359432184006 [HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request 926ms]
{noformat}

I think the behaviour should be the same as when I try to do this query: 'text !~ foo'
{quote}
The operator '!~' is not supported by the 'text' field.
{quote}
{panel}

h3. Summary
When searching for "_NOT text_" in the *Issue Navigator*, JIRA will show "no results" rather than displaying an error message saying that it is not possible to use "NOT text".

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an issue and add "Text" to its description
# Open the Issue Navigator
# Search for:
{noformat}
NOT text ~ "text"
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
JIRA would show a warning message similarly to what is displayed when trying to search for "text !~ text":
bq. The operator '!~' is not supported by the 'text' field.

h3. Actual Results
JIRA always returns with no results.

*Rating*: :) Good

