In a case where Stash was connected to JIRA and it was not possible to push in the {{http://user@stash:7990/repo}} format, it was found that this was due to IIS. JIRA uses a 400 response code with a specific message in the body to indicate to Stash that authentication for a particular user has failed. But it appears the response body and content-type are being mangled by some idiosyncratic IIS behaviour, detailed here: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3993941/in-iis7-5-what-module-removes-the-body-of-a-400-bad-request

Perhaps the ["Integrating JIRA with IIS" page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Integrating+JIRA+with+IIS] should include the answer from the URL above.

