By setting up an application link between JIRA and Confluence, when a user add a JIRA issue macro in a page, a remote issue link will be automatically created in the issue. However if we delete the linked page in Confluence, or remove the JIRA issue macro in the issue itself, the remote link will still remain in the issue. 

Hence, it will be great if the remote link is automatically removed as well if the linked Confluence page is deleted or when the JIRA issue macro is removed from the page, or at least prompt the user to either retain the link or remove it.

